from\": 540, \"to\": 552}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"In these difficult times we are living through, with wars and conflicts on the rise, people are fed up with all the hate, the aggression and negative news they are facing day in and day out,\\\" International Olympic Committee (IOC) President Thomas Bach said in his speech.\", \"from\": 575, \"to\": 847, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"these difficult times\", \"from\": 579, \"to\": 600}, {\"ngram\": \"wars\", \"from\": 629, \"to\": 633}, {\"ngram\": \"conflicts\", \"from\": 638, \"to\": 647}, {\"ngram\": \"the rise\", \"from\": 651, \"to\": 659}, {\"ngram\": \"people\", \"from\": 661, \"to\": 667}, {\"ngram\": \"all the hate\", \"from\": 684, \"to\": 696}, {\"ngram\": \"the aggression\", \"from\": 698, \"to\": 712}, {\"ngram\": \"negative news\", \"from\": 717, \"to\": 730}, {\"ngram\": \"IOC\", \"from\": 801, \"to\": 804}, {\"ngram\": \"his speech\", \"from\": 836, \"to\": 846}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We are longing for something which brings us together, something that is unifying, something that gives us hope.\", \"from\": 849, \"to\": 962, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 869, \"to\": 878}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 892, \"to\": 894}, {\"ngram\": \"something\", \"from\": 933, \"to\": 942}, {\"ngram\": \"us\", \"from\": 954, \"to\": 956}, {\"ngram\": \"hope\", \"from\": 957, \"to\": 961}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Olympic flame that we are lighting today is the symbol of this hope.\\\"\", \"from\": 963, \"to\": 1036, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 967, \"end\": 980, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_flame\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 3.8337628851279916e-22, \"text\": \"Olympic flame\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_flame\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_flame\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the symbol\", \"from\": 1011, \"to\": 1021}, {\"ngram\": \"this hope\", \"from\": 1025, \"to\": 1034}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The torch of the first runner of the relay, Greece's Olympic rowing champion Stefanos Ntouskos, was then lit by Mina.\", \"from\": 1038, \"to\": 1155, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1082, \"end\": 1088, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"score\": 0.9987992820894347, \"rank\": 0.0012021255263244051, \"text\": \"Greece\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Greece\"}, {\"begin\": 1115, \"end\": 1132, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stefanos_Ntouskos\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Stefanos Ntouskos\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stefanos_Ntouskos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stefanos_Ntouskos\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The torch\", \"from\": 1038, \"to\": 1047}, {\"ngram\": \"the first runner\", \"from\": 1051, \"to\": 1067}, {\"ngram\": \"the relay\", \"from\": 1071, \"to\": 1080}, {\"ngram\": \"Mina\", \"from\": 1150, \"to\": 1154}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Ntouskos then handed the flame, after a short run, to France's three-time Olympic medallist in swimming and head of Paris' Olympic torch relay, Laure Manaudou, as the representative of the host city.\", \"from\": 1157, \"to\": 1356, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1211, \"end\": 1217, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999988455044629, \"rank\": 6.734325430363732e-07, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1273, \"end\": 1278, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999997094164, \"rank\": 2.905964854976728e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1301, \"end\": 1315, \"title\": \"h